WEBVTT

00:01:36.680 --> 00:01:37.240
Jia.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:39.880
I was looking at the stars last night.

00:01:39.880 --> 00:01:41.160
Guess what I saw.

00:01:41.160 --> 00:01:42.090
What did you see?

00:01:43.320 --> 00:01:44.920
I saw that your back hurts.

00:01:46.720 --> 00:01:49.120
Yeah, my back hasn't been great lately.

00:01:49.360 --> 00:01:50.200
It hurts a bit.

00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:51.600
Let me show you a couple of tricks.

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:53.640
It's a secret technique passed down in the Wu family.

00:01:53.640 --> 00:01:54.880
I'm only the second generation to know it.

00:01:54.880 --> 00:01:55.440
Come on.

00:01:56.280 --> 00:01:58.360
Imagine you're driving a taxi.

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:00.240
Come on.

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:02.060
Driving a taxi.

00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:04.720
Drive, drive, drive.

00:02:05.320 --> 00:02:07.320
You have to shake. You have to shake.

00:02:07.800 --> 00:02:09.240
Let your upper body shake.

00:02:09.240 --> 00:02:09.840
Like this?

00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:11.460
Too much. Too much.

00:02:12.320 --> 00:02:13.980
Red light. Step on the brakes.

00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:16.440
Did you step on it?

00:02:16.880 --> 00:02:17.560
Kick out.

00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:20.180
Use your right hand

00:02:21.840 --> 00:02:23.240
to reach your left waist.

00:02:23.440 --> 00:02:24.120
Reach hard.

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:25.920
Right hand reaching left waist.

00:02:25.960 --> 00:02:27.160
Look straight ahead.

00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:29.000
Then use your right shoulder

00:02:29.560 --> 00:02:31.560
to lean towards your left shoulder.

00:02:33.040 --> 00:02:33.770
Did it crack?

00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:35.040
It cracked. It cracked.

00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:35.680
Yes.

00:02:36.160 --> 00:02:37.560
Keep driving. Keep driving. Keep driving.

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:38.760
Keep driving. Drive.

00:02:39.440 --> 00:02:40.120
Red light.

00:02:40.920 --> 00:02:41.780
Hit the brakes.

00:02:42.079 --> 00:02:43.440
Now do the opposite.

00:02:43.720 --> 00:02:46.320
Reach for your right waist with your left hand.

00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:47.880
Reach for the right waist.

00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:50.880
Lean your left shoulder against your right shoulder.

00:02:52.480 --> 00:02:53.210
Did it crack?

00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:54.720
It cracked.

00:02:54.720 --> 00:02:56.450
Let me teach you another trick.

00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:57.960
Keep driving. Keep driving. Keep driving.

00:02:57.960 --> 00:02:58.760
Keep driving.

00:02:58.800 --> 00:02:59.660
Start driving.

00:03:00.440 --> 00:03:01.440
The light turns green.

00:03:01.440 --> 00:03:03.640
Should we shift gears first?

00:03:04.280 --> 00:03:04.920
Right?

00:03:05.680 --> 00:03:06.760
There's no gear stick.

00:03:06.760 --> 00:03:07.440
Here.

00:03:07.960 --> 00:03:08.890
This is the gear.

00:03:09.040 --> 00:03:10.970
Shift from neutral to drive first.

00:03:12.200 --> 00:03:13.480
Just shift this.

00:03:14.800 --> 00:03:16.760
From neutral to drive.

00:03:17.440 --> 00:03:18.720
One, two, three.

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:19.760
Drive.

00:03:19.760 --> 00:03:20.690
It's not moving.

00:03:20.960 --> 00:03:22.280
You didn't step on the gas.

00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:23.140
Step on the gas.

00:03:23.160 --> 00:03:24.000
I have to step on the gas too.

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:24.640
Yes.

00:03:24.760 --> 00:03:25.960
Gas. One, two, three.

00:03:26.760 --> 00:03:27.720
The pushback.

00:03:28.880 --> 00:03:29.400
Why did

00:03:31.280 --> 00:03:32.320
it not ring?

00:03:33.360 --> 00:03:34.480
Because

00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:36.010
I was just messing with you.

00:03:38.400 --> 00:03:39.280
Wu Wei,

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:43.240
you're unbelievable.

00:03:47.480 --> 00:03:48.440
Come on.

00:03:48.640 --> 00:03:50.040
How's your little lame leg doing?

00:03:50.040 --> 00:03:50.700
Any better?

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:52.160
It's fine.

00:03:53.040 --> 00:03:53.900
Just a scratch.

00:03:56.960 --> 00:03:57.840
Seriously,

00:03:58.440 --> 00:04:00.160
your first launch,

00:04:00.720 --> 00:04:01.960
how do you feel?

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:05.040
For my first mission,

00:04:05.280 --> 00:04:06.560
going through so much,

00:04:06.920 --> 00:04:07.840
to be honest,

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:10.530
it's quite unforgettable.

00:04:11.360 --> 00:04:12.960
That's how aerospace works.

00:04:13.080 --> 00:04:13.960
Every success

00:04:13.960 --> 00:04:15.680
is built on

00:04:15.680 --> 00:04:17.010
failure after failure.

00:04:17.440 --> 00:04:19.160
Man proposes, God disposes.

00:04:19.480 --> 00:04:20.959
So there will always be

00:04:20.959 --> 00:04:22.160
unexpected things

00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:23.720
happening during missions.

00:04:23.720 --> 00:04:26.780
The most important thing is to have contingency plans.

00:04:28.160 --> 00:04:29.400
From this launch,

00:04:29.680 --> 00:04:31.280
I have one huge realization.

00:04:32.640 --> 00:04:33.480
That is,

00:04:34.440 --> 00:04:36.760
I know I truly love this job.

00:04:37.440 --> 00:04:39.320
And it's something I will always

00:04:39.800 --> 00:04:41.060
keep doing from now on.

00:04:43.920 --> 00:04:45.080
I just don't know

00:04:45.720 --> 00:04:47.600
if Tumen-2 can be saved.

00:04:51.640 --> 00:04:52.520
I believe that

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:56.120
as long as we work hard, stay focused and meticulous,

00:04:56.720 --> 00:04:58.780
we can definitely solve the problem.

00:05:01.640 --> 00:05:03.040
All right, go get busy.

00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:03.800
Okay.

00:05:03.800 --> 00:05:04.400
Go.

00:05:15.200 --> 00:05:18.520
The velocity increment for this mid-course correction is 1.6 meters per second.

00:05:18.520 --> 00:05:20.560
The nominal burn time is 4.2 seconds.

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:21.800
Activate the 20N thruster.

00:05:21.800 --> 00:05:22.560
Yes.

00:05:22.720 --> 00:05:24.380
Activating the 20N thruster.

00:05:27.440 --> 00:05:28.480
Repeating 20N.

00:05:28.480 --> 00:05:30.160
Nominal burn 4.2 seconds.

00:05:30.480 --> 00:05:32.760
20N, 4.2 seconds.

00:05:35.080 --> 00:05:35.960
Repeating 20N.

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.800
Nominal burn 4.2 seconds.

00:05:45.880 --> 00:05:48.360
According to telemetry, the mid-course correction is complete.

00:05:48.360 --> 00:05:49.880
Satellite status is normal.

00:05:49.880 --> 00:05:51.940
Entering stellar orientation mode.

00:05:54.960 --> 00:05:55.920
Sending commands.

00:05:55.920 --> 00:05:57.680
Entering sun orientation mode.

00:05:57.680 --> 00:05:59.010
Correction completed.

00:05:59.240 --> 00:05:59.880
Good.

00:06:09.440 --> 00:06:10.840
That was not easy.

00:06:22.680 --> 00:06:25.080
From the Xichang Satellite Launch Center,

00:06:25.520 --> 00:06:25.880
using the Zhengtu-4C

00:06:25.880 --> 00:06:27.280
carrier rocket, our country

00:06:27.280 --> 00:06:30.080
successfully launched the lunar exploration project's Haoyue-4 mission,

00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:32.480
the Xingqiao relay satellite, into space.

00:06:32.520 --> 00:06:33.720
The Xingqiao relay satellite

00:06:33.720 --> 00:06:35.520
will provide Earth-Moon relay communication

00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:37.920
for the Haoyue-4 lunar exploration mission

00:06:37.920 --> 00:06:39.960
planned for later this year.

00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:41.760
This is also the first time

00:06:41.760 --> 00:06:44.760
a human spacecraft operates in orbit at the Earth-Moon L2 point.

00:06:44.760 --> 00:06:45.680
News: The satellite, launched via the Zhengtu-4C carrier rocket from the Xichang Satellite Launch Center, will reach the Earth-Moon Lagrange point 450,000 kilometers from Earth in over 20 days.

00:06:45.680 --> 00:06:45.840
News: The satellite, launched via the Zhengtu-4 carrier rocket from Xichang, will reach the Earth-Moon Lagrange point L2 450,000 kilometers from Earth in over 20 days.

00:06:45.840 --> 00:06:46.760
Launched via the Zhengtu-4C carrier rocket from the Xichang Satellite Launch Center, the satellite heads for the far side of the moon and will reach the Earth-Moon Lagrange point L2, 450,000 kilometers from Earth, in over 20 days.

00:06:46.760 --> 00:06:49.120
Every subsequent step is also crucial

00:06:49.120 --> 00:06:50.040
just to ensure our entire Haoyue-4 mission.

00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:50.920
Great.

00:06:51.200 --> 00:06:52.640
It finally succeeded.

00:06:52.640 --> 00:06:54.640
My heart almost couldn't take it.

00:06:55.880 --> 00:06:58.240
But with this on Xiao Qi's resume,

00:06:58.240 --> 00:06:59.720
he can apply to more good schools

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:02.280
for further studies abroad in the future.

00:07:02.880 --> 00:07:03.400
No.

00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:06.200
Why do you still want him to keep studying?

00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:08.360
I think he's doing great at the Flight Control Center right now.

00:07:08.360 --> 00:07:10.080
People always aim higher, you know?

00:07:10.080 --> 00:07:11.240
He's so young.

00:07:11.240 --> 00:07:14.840
There will be plenty of good opportunities for him in the future.

00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:16.740
What are you thinking?

00:07:24.720 --> 00:07:25.720
Xiao Qu, Caibao.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:28.560
Your scores for the previous round

00:07:28.560 --> 00:07:29.880
of fault contingency plans

00:07:29.880 --> 00:07:30.810
are already out.

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:32.040
It's just that because we entered the mission,

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:33.920
I didn't have time to inform you.

00:07:34.440 --> 00:07:35.240
Mr. Jiang.

00:07:35.960 --> 00:07:37.440
Did I fail again?

00:07:38.240 --> 00:07:39.570
It's fine. Just tell me.

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:44.600
You did very well this round

00:07:44.600 --> 00:07:46.000
and got very high scores.

00:07:46.680 --> 00:07:47.320
Why?

00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:48.280
Didn't you feel your own progress

00:07:48.280 --> 00:07:50.120
during the mission?

00:07:51.960 --> 00:07:53.200
One is proficient in algorithms,

00:07:53.200 --> 00:07:54.640
and the other is good at programming.

00:07:54.640 --> 00:07:56.680
As long as you two can cooperate well,

00:07:56.680 --> 00:07:59.340
I believe we can definitely solve the problems.

00:08:01.640 --> 00:08:02.280
Let's go.

00:08:22.320 --> 00:08:23.080
Mr. Chu,

00:08:23.160 --> 00:08:24.720
Mr. Wu, Mr. Ying.

00:08:27.520 --> 00:08:28.720
Thank you, teachers.

00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:29.400
You're welcome.

00:08:29.400 --> 00:08:30.440
It's what we should do.

00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:31.320
We must.

00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:33.200
You saved our Tumen-2.

00:08:33.200 --> 00:08:34.960
You are our heroes.

00:08:34.960 --> 00:08:36.520
Yeah. Right. Yes.

00:08:36.520 --> 00:08:37.240
Teachers,

00:08:37.480 --> 00:08:38.960
we have a small gift

00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:39.840
for you.

00:08:41.320 --> 00:08:43.280
This is a photo of the Earth and the Moon

00:08:43.280 --> 00:08:45.040
just taken by Tumen-2.

00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:47.200
There's no photo shop to print it now,

00:08:47.200 --> 00:08:48.600
so we'll show you first.

00:08:48.600 --> 00:08:49.400
Because of you,

00:08:49.400 --> 00:08:50.840
we have such a picture.

00:08:51.280 --> 00:08:52.880
It's nothing. You're welcome.

00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:53.800
Everyone has worked hard.

00:08:53.800 --> 00:08:54.960
Go back and rest.

00:08:56.320 --> 00:08:56.880
Let's go.

00:09:00.640 --> 00:09:01.400
I'm hungry.

00:09:02.120 --> 00:09:04.050
Then let's go get something to eat.

00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:08.700
Flight control is so good. I can't bear to leave.

00:09:09.760 --> 00:09:11.000
That's true.

00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:14.280
Our regular employment list should be announced.

00:09:14.640 --> 00:09:15.640
What a beautiful moment.

00:09:15.640 --> 00:09:17.640
You have to bring up such a buzzkill?

00:09:19.680 --> 00:09:22.120
But anyway, we've tried our best.

00:09:23.080 --> 00:09:24.480
No matter what the result is.

00:09:24.480 --> 00:09:26.140
If it really doesn't work out,

00:09:26.800 --> 00:09:28.660
then it's our own lack of ability.

00:09:29.120 --> 00:09:29.840
No.

00:09:30.440 --> 00:09:32.640
I think you are very good and excellent.

00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:36.720
I think we are all very good

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:38.360
and excellent.

00:09:39.240 --> 00:09:41.800
Okay, all excellent.

00:09:42.720 --> 00:09:43.450
How about it?

00:09:43.840 --> 00:09:46.280
My people are great, right?

00:09:47.960 --> 00:09:49.720
Look at your level of awareness.

00:09:49.720 --> 00:09:50.480
Your people?

00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:52.480
They are all national talents,

00:09:52.480 --> 00:09:53.840
pillars of the state.

00:09:54.040 --> 00:09:55.560
Alright, yours.

00:09:58.360 --> 00:09:59.480
The mission is completed.

00:09:59.480 --> 00:10:01.480
You have to treat me to steamed buns.

00:10:02.440 --> 00:10:04.200
Treating to a meal is a must.

00:10:04.600 --> 00:10:05.280
But this time,

00:10:05.280 --> 00:10:06.680
I think you should treat.

00:10:06.920 --> 00:10:08.720
Why me? I treated last time.

00:10:08.720 --> 00:10:10.000
You remembered it wrong.

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:10.800
You're cheating.

00:10:10.800 --> 00:10:11.360
No.

00:10:11.560 --> 00:10:12.840
I really treated last time.

00:10:12.840 --> 00:10:13.480
What's wrong?

00:10:13.480 --> 00:10:14.040
Look.

00:10:14.240 --> 00:10:17.120
That was a long, long time ago,

00:10:17.120 --> 00:10:17.600
right?

00:10:17.600 --> 00:10:18.120
Right.

00:10:18.440 --> 00:10:20.100
You used my meal tickets then.

00:10:21.160 --> 00:10:21.800
Since

00:10:22.440 --> 00:10:24.720
it's a long time ago,

00:10:24.720 --> 00:10:26.080
how do you remember it so clearly?

00:10:26.080 --> 00:10:27.360
I have a small notebook,

00:10:27.360 --> 00:10:30.120
specially recording your every little thing.

00:10:30.800 --> 00:10:32.080
You are too sneaky.

00:10:32.080 --> 00:10:34.080
Okay. I'll treat.

00:10:34.320 --> 00:10:35.600
You should treat.

00:10:36.240 --> 00:10:38.480
Let's just go find the leader

00:10:38.480 --> 00:10:39.480
and let him treat.

00:10:40.280 --> 00:10:42.120
Right. Let him treat us to roast duck.

00:10:42.120 --> 00:10:42.800
Extort him a good meal.

00:10:42.800 --> 00:10:44.120
Rip him off.

00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:02.200
You go.

00:11:11.560 --> 00:11:12.200
My leg.

00:11:12.200 --> 00:11:13.600
Alright. I'll go.

00:11:14.280 --> 00:11:14.880
Coming.

00:11:22.800 --> 00:11:23.400
I'm sorry.

00:11:23.400 --> 00:11:25.280
I told him it's too early,

00:11:25.280 --> 00:11:26.720
but he insisted on coming.

00:11:26.720 --> 00:11:27.720
He's getting excited over nothing.

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:29.480
What do you mean excited over nothing?

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:30.680
Where is Brother Wei?

00:11:30.880 --> 00:11:33.080
Brother Wei, this is very important.

00:11:33.080 --> 00:11:34.840
I have some important news to announce to you all.

00:11:34.840 --> 00:11:35.320
What's going on?

00:11:35.320 --> 00:11:36.600
Come here.

00:11:38.640 --> 00:11:40.640
Weren't you not limping yesterday?

00:11:40.760 --> 00:11:41.560
Have a seat.

00:11:42.320 --> 00:11:42.960
Thank you.

00:11:44.600 --> 00:11:45.200
What's up?

00:11:46.960 --> 00:11:49.420
The list of regular employees is finalized.

00:11:49.880 --> 00:11:52.080
I heard the leaders already discussed it.

00:11:52.080 --> 00:11:54.320
We're just waiting for the announcement.

00:11:54.320 --> 00:11:55.000
That fast?

00:11:55.280 --> 00:11:55.880
Who is it?

00:12:03.040 --> 00:12:04.720
A message from Mr. Qin.

00:12:06.760 --> 00:12:07.960
Did they announce it?

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:08.930
What does it say?

00:12:12.240 --> 00:12:13.520
How about...

00:12:15.360 --> 00:12:16.040
Brother Qi.

00:12:17.120 --> 00:12:18.760
How about you listen?

00:12:19.040 --> 00:12:20.500
You're not afraid anyway.

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:21.840
Among us,

00:12:21.840 --> 00:12:23.570
you're the most likely to stay.

00:12:23.680 --> 00:12:24.810
I don't want to look.

00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:28.520
I'll do it. Whatever.

00:12:37.280 --> 00:12:38.280
Are you all up?

00:12:38.440 --> 00:12:39.960
I have something to tell you.

00:12:39.960 --> 00:12:40.880
Over the next few days,

00:12:40.880 --> 00:12:44.010
there's an aerospace week event at the exhibition hall.

00:12:44.120 --> 00:12:45.880
It's hosted by our New Media Center,

00:12:45.880 --> 00:12:47.520
"Our Space."

00:12:47.920 --> 00:12:49.520
Flight Control also has a booth.

00:12:49.520 --> 00:12:50.880
If you guys are free,

00:12:50.880 --> 00:12:52.120
you can go have some fun.

00:12:52.120 --> 00:12:54.000
And help out while you're at it.

00:12:54.320 --> 00:12:55.400
The mission was tiring,

00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:57.060
so just treat it as a vacation.

00:12:57.120 --> 00:12:59.200
Also, there's a small competition.

00:12:59.200 --> 00:13:01.520
You can act as instructors.

00:13:02.960 --> 00:13:04.400
Old Qin said he's giving us a break.

00:13:04.400 --> 00:13:06.440
How about we go and have some fun?

00:13:07.960 --> 00:13:08.600
Yeah.

00:13:08.600 --> 00:13:09.800
We'll find out sooner or later anyway.

00:13:09.800 --> 00:13:10.640
Being afraid won't help.

00:13:10.640 --> 00:13:12.680
Besides, you have to think about it this way.

00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:13.280
Out of the four of us,

00:13:13.280 --> 00:13:15.280
one of us will be able to stay, right?

00:13:18.920 --> 00:13:19.980
Get ready to go out.

00:13:21.440 --> 00:13:23.300
I'll get you guys some breakfast.

00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:03.520
How is it?

00:14:05.480 --> 00:14:06.520
I'm not bragging.

00:14:06.920 --> 00:14:08.200
I don't even need to guide anything.

00:14:08.200 --> 00:14:09.480
We will definitely be the champions tomorrow.

00:14:09.480 --> 00:14:11.280
Pride goes before a fall, understand?

00:14:11.280 --> 00:14:12.400
I won't say anything more.

00:14:12.400 --> 00:14:14.120
Let's see who's better on the field.

00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:14.760
Sure.

00:14:15.960 --> 00:14:16.820
What time is it?

00:14:18.280 --> 00:14:19.140
Eleven thirty.

00:14:19.880 --> 00:14:21.210
Oh no, we're out of time.

00:14:21.560 --> 00:14:22.360
What's wrong?

00:14:22.360 --> 00:14:23.240
They are redeeming Fat Five today.

00:14:23.240 --> 00:14:24.300
I have to go get one.

00:14:25.760 --> 00:14:28.760
For those who want to redeem the Long March 5 model,

00:14:29.160 --> 00:14:31.560
please come to our space booth,

00:14:31.560 --> 00:14:32.760
line up orderly,

00:14:32.760 --> 00:14:34.000
and redeem it with your admission ticket.

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:34.640
Thank you.

00:14:34.840 --> 00:14:37.000
The giant model in the center of the exhibition hall

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:37.440
Hold it carefully.

00:14:37.440 --> 00:14:39.320
is the Long March 5, a large cryogenic liquid

00:14:39.320 --> 00:14:39.960
Thank you.

00:14:39.960 --> 00:14:43.560
bundled two-and-a-half-stage launch vehicle.

00:14:43.880 --> 00:14:46.480
The total length of the rocket is 56.97 meters.

00:14:46.840 --> 00:14:49.640
The takeoff mass is about 869 tons.

00:14:49.880 --> 00:14:52.480
It has a payload capacity of 25 tons to low Earth orbit

00:14:52.480 --> 00:14:55.200
and 14 tons to geosynchronous transfer orbit.

00:14:56.360 --> 00:14:58.880
It can complete launch missions for various spacecraft,

00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:01.200
including low Earth orbit satellites, geosynchronous transfer orbit satellites,

00:15:01.200 --> 00:15:03.240
sun-synchronous orbit satellites,

00:15:03.240 --> 00:15:05.440
space stations, lunar probes,

00:15:05.600 --> 00:15:07.240
and Mars probes.

00:15:10.080 --> 00:15:12.340
The Long March 5 was officially approved

00:15:12.440 --> 00:15:13.960
for development in 2006.

00:15:14.280 --> 00:15:16.480
On November 3, 2016,

00:15:16.480 --> 00:15:19.440
the Long March 5 was successfully launched for the first time

00:15:19.440 --> 00:15:21.370
at the Wenchang Space Launch Site,

00:15:21.480 --> 00:15:25.140
sending experimental satellites into their designated orbits.

00:15:25.280 --> 00:15:25.880
Two,

00:15:25.880 --> 00:15:26.940
please. Thank you.

00:15:27.960 --> 00:15:29.160
Sorry, they're gone.

00:15:34.920 --> 00:15:36.520
Bro, I'll help you with that.

00:15:36.680 --> 00:15:37.480
Okay, thanks.

00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:38.180
No problem.

00:15:39.680 --> 00:15:40.280
Hello?

00:15:41.440 --> 00:15:44.280
I'm at the Yuanli booth.

00:15:44.760 --> 00:15:46.020
I'll wait for you here.

00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:48.840
Thanks.

00:15:49.240 --> 00:15:50.000
Bro.

00:15:50.320 --> 00:15:51.880
Can I talk to you about something?

00:15:51.880 --> 00:15:53.280
It's about this model.

00:15:53.280 --> 00:15:54.920
Can you sell one to me?

00:15:55.280 --> 00:15:56.140
I'll pay extra.

00:15:56.960 --> 00:15:57.640
Sorry.

00:15:57.640 --> 00:15:59.600
Not for sale. I'm giving it to someone.

00:15:59.600 --> 00:16:00.200
No.

00:16:00.760 --> 00:16:02.480
Actually, this model

00:16:02.720 --> 00:16:04.440
was supposed to be mine.

00:16:05.960 --> 00:16:07.290
Listen, let me explain.

00:16:07.880 --> 00:16:09.480
Just now downstairs,

00:16:09.480 --> 00:16:11.140
while queuing for the models,

00:16:11.600 --> 00:16:12.800
I zoned out.

00:16:12.800 --> 00:16:14.640
I was watching some videos on the big screen,

00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:15.320
and right then,

00:16:15.320 --> 00:16:16.880
you suddenly appeared in front of me.

00:16:16.880 --> 00:16:18.000
I was going to say something to you,

00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:19.800
but I saw the number of models and people

00:16:19.800 --> 00:16:20.600
matched exactly.

00:16:20.600 --> 00:16:22.000
So, I didn't think much of it.

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:24.040
But I didn't expect you to have two tickets.

00:16:24.040 --> 00:16:25.040
You took both of them,

00:16:25.040 --> 00:16:26.360
and there was none left for me.

00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:27.760
Yeah, that's what I mean.

00:16:27.960 --> 00:16:28.600
Of course,

00:16:29.240 --> 00:16:31.720
I'm not saying you cut in line on purpose.

00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:33.080
But this model

00:16:33.080 --> 00:16:34.960
is really important to me.

00:16:36.200 --> 00:16:38.400
I've been waiting for it for a long time.

00:16:38.840 --> 00:16:40.920
Well, according to what you said,

00:16:42.280 --> 00:16:43.640
I really should give you one.

00:16:43.640 --> 00:16:44.880
I wouldn't say 'give'.

00:16:44.880 --> 00:16:46.200
Since you have two,

00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:46.960
you can spare me one,

00:16:46.960 --> 00:16:48.820
and we'll have one each. Perfect.

00:16:49.400 --> 00:16:50.730
But I don't believe you.

00:17:10.640 --> 00:17:12.040
You like their stuff too?

00:17:12.720 --> 00:17:13.880
I'm a huge fan.

00:17:17.480 --> 00:17:17.960
Seriously.

00:17:17.960 --> 00:17:19.560
Man, why are you still following me?

00:17:19.560 --> 00:17:20.720
I'm really not selling it.

00:17:20.720 --> 00:17:21.720
Let's just chat.

00:17:21.960 --> 00:17:22.440
Um...

00:17:22.440 --> 00:17:24.599
Do you like their design style,

00:17:24.599 --> 00:17:26.319
or what?

00:17:27.160 --> 00:17:29.240
I really like their founder.

00:17:29.240 --> 00:17:31.170
You can tell he's a true space geek.

00:17:31.680 --> 00:17:35.080
And their brand management is pretty good.

00:17:35.800 --> 00:17:36.640
Good taste.

00:17:38.040 --> 00:17:38.720
I managed to grab two.

00:17:38.720 --> 00:17:39.480
Are they for me?

00:17:39.480 --> 00:17:41.610
They are yours. Give me the errand fee.

00:17:45.600 --> 00:17:47.000
Let me introduce myself.

00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:48.960
My name is Xu Xu.

00:17:54.440 --> 00:17:55.640
The manager of Force?

00:17:56.600 --> 00:17:57.480
That's me.

00:17:57.840 --> 00:17:58.970
What a coincidence.

00:17:59.560 --> 00:18:01.440
Since you are my loyal fan,

00:18:01.720 --> 00:18:03.520
pick one you like. It's my treat.

00:18:05.040 --> 00:18:06.480
That doesn't seem right. Then I...

00:18:06.480 --> 00:18:09.040
It depends on how you look at it.

00:18:10.680 --> 00:18:13.080
If you really feel bad about it,

00:18:13.360 --> 00:18:14.090
why don't you

00:18:15.160 --> 00:18:16.490
exchange it for a model?

00:18:19.800 --> 00:18:20.920
So that's what you were waiting for.

00:18:20.920 --> 00:18:21.560
Forget it.

00:18:21.560 --> 00:18:22.890
No, wait a minute. Um...

00:18:23.120 --> 00:18:25.360
What do you think of this drone?

00:18:25.360 --> 00:18:27.090
I designed it myself this year.

00:18:27.160 --> 00:18:27.720
It's for you.

00:18:27.720 --> 00:18:28.600
No, no, no.

00:18:28.600 --> 00:18:29.800
Let me take a look.

00:18:33.960 --> 00:18:35.720
There's a problem with the design.

00:18:35.720 --> 00:18:37.180
The proportions seem off.

00:18:37.240 --> 00:18:38.400
Look at its rotors.

00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:41.360
It feels like it'll tilt when flying.

00:18:41.720 --> 00:18:42.580
What happened?

00:18:42.960 --> 00:18:43.880
You're slipping.

00:18:43.880 --> 00:18:45.160
Don't get cocky, okay?

00:18:45.240 --> 00:18:47.040
Come on, what do you know?

00:18:47.040 --> 00:18:48.400
Let's fly it and see.

00:18:50.640 --> 00:18:51.770
Let me fly it for you.

00:18:51.960 --> 00:18:52.720
Okay, fly it.

00:19:26.040 --> 00:19:27.240
Let me tell you,

00:19:28.040 --> 00:19:29.120
this is a prototype

00:19:29.600 --> 00:19:30.680
and a new model.

00:19:31.120 --> 00:19:33.450
The staff don't know how to operate it yet,

00:19:33.480 --> 00:19:35.440
which is why that happened.

00:19:37.080 --> 00:19:38.080
Let me take a look.

00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:40.720
It's just a problem with the internal circuit.

00:19:40.720 --> 00:19:42.250
I just need to tweak it a bit.

00:19:43.280 --> 00:19:44.000
Let me tell you,

00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:44.880
my products

00:19:44.880 --> 00:19:46.880
usually don't have problems.

00:19:47.400 --> 00:19:48.240
For so many years,

00:19:48.240 --> 00:19:50.880
all customer feedback has been good.

00:19:51.480 --> 00:19:52.640
They are all positive reviews,

00:19:52.640 --> 00:19:54.370
without a single negative one.

00:19:56.480 --> 00:19:58.240
Okay, let's try again.

00:20:03.920 --> 00:20:07.380
The Star of the Future Rocket Competition officially begins!

00:20:08.320 --> 00:20:10.600
The judges will comprehensively score the appearance of the rocket model,

00:20:10.600 --> 00:20:12.640
its attitude control during takeoff,

00:20:12.640 --> 00:20:15.080
and its hang time in the air

00:20:15.080 --> 00:20:16.400
and other aspects.

00:20:16.600 --> 00:20:17.800
Yangfan Middle School Team.

00:20:17.800 --> 00:20:18.960
Skygazing Enthusiasts Team.

00:20:18.960 --> 00:20:20.420
Come on, come on. Let's go.

00:20:28.040 --> 00:20:30.000
Let's go.

00:20:30.400 --> 00:20:32.040
Three, two, one,

00:20:32.160 --> 00:20:32.800
launch.

00:20:41.520 --> 00:20:42.520
Just watch.

00:20:42.840 --> 00:20:43.480
Bring it on.

00:20:43.480 --> 00:20:44.960
See how we'll beat you.

00:20:50.920 --> 00:20:51.920
In position,

00:20:51.920 --> 00:20:52.560
launch.

00:20:56.480 --> 00:20:57.280
Look.

00:20:58.280 --> 00:20:59.080
Look at that.

00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:04.200
So cool!

00:21:06.240 --> 00:21:08.900
If some people hadn't dragged us down back then,

00:21:08.920 --> 00:21:10.160
we would've been the champions too.

00:21:10.160 --> 00:21:12.160
You were the one who dragged us down.

00:21:15.760 --> 00:21:18.320
It seems there's still one team that hasn't launched.

00:21:18.320 --> 00:21:20.040
They still haven't launched by now.

00:21:20.040 --> 00:21:21.560
I guess they have no chance.

00:21:21.560 --> 00:21:23.040
Who said they have no chance?

00:21:23.040 --> 00:21:24.440
The competition isn't over yet.

00:21:24.440 --> 00:21:25.370
What's the rush?

00:21:26.240 --> 00:21:26.770
Let's go.

00:21:31.160 --> 00:21:31.800
Wei, Qi.

00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:34.520
Middle schoolers can play with three-stage rockets now.

00:21:34.520 --> 00:21:36.240
That's a rule violation, right?

00:21:36.240 --> 00:21:37.170
I don't think so.

00:21:44.280 --> 00:21:45.640
01, wind speed normal.

00:21:45.760 --> 00:21:47.440
02, ignition wire normal.

00:21:47.760 --> 00:21:49.290
03, rocketeer in position.

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:51.720
Launch.

00:22:00.080 --> 00:22:01.480
Go! Go!

00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:02.240
Go!

00:22:16.840 --> 00:22:19.360
I heard you guys are from the flight control center.

00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:20.120
What's up?

00:22:21.000 --> 00:22:22.240
I saw your rocket.

00:22:22.960 --> 00:22:23.890
The idea is good.

00:22:24.240 --> 00:22:26.600
But the execution is a bit underwhelming.

00:22:27.080 --> 00:22:29.240
Have you fixed that drone of yours?

00:22:32.520 --> 00:22:33.400
That's him?

00:22:33.400 --> 00:22:34.330
I'm telling you.

00:22:34.640 --> 00:22:36.160
Don't bring that up.

00:22:38.840 --> 00:22:40.080
I heard you newbies

00:22:40.080 --> 00:22:41.760
call yourselves Team Muxing.

00:22:43.640 --> 00:22:44.440
Interesting.

00:22:44.840 --> 00:22:47.100
Let's compete again if there's a chance.

00:22:50.400 --> 00:22:51.600
You owe me a model.

00:22:56.040 --> 00:22:58.640
I announce that this competition

00:22:58.640 --> 00:23:00.920
has successfully concluded.

00:23:23.360 --> 00:23:24.820
Look at your phones. Look!

00:23:28.200 --> 00:23:31.640
After a unanimous decision by the Flight Control Center leaders,

00:23:31.640 --> 00:23:33.400
it is now officially approved that

00:23:33.400 --> 00:23:34.530
comrades Ying Ziqi,

00:23:35.280 --> 00:23:35.920
Wu Wei,

00:23:35.920 --> 00:23:36.880
Qu Ruonan,

00:23:37.120 --> 00:23:38.440
and Cai Bo'ao

00:23:38.440 --> 00:23:41.160
are officially confirmed on schedule,

00:23:41.160 --> 00:23:43.490
and will take up their posts immediately.

00:23:47.920 --> 00:23:48.800
This is so cool.

00:24:17.480 --> 00:24:17.840
Come on.

00:24:17.840 --> 00:24:19.680
In the future, our Star-herding Team

00:24:19.680 --> 00:24:21.480
will conquer the moon and Mars.

00:24:21.480 --> 00:24:22.600
Cheers.

00:24:28.240 --> 00:24:29.440
There are no seats inside.

00:24:29.440 --> 00:24:30.280
No seats left.

00:24:30.280 --> 00:24:31.080
There are only four of us.

00:24:31.080 --> 00:24:31.680
Right.

00:24:32.160 --> 00:24:32.720
Jia.

00:24:34.720 --> 00:24:35.360
Jia.

00:24:37.400 --> 00:24:38.440
Let's eat together here.

00:24:38.440 --> 00:24:39.440
They are here.

00:24:41.680 --> 00:24:42.840
You guys are unbelievable,

00:24:42.840 --> 00:24:43.720
eating without us.

00:24:43.720 --> 00:24:44.360
Exactly.

00:24:44.360 --> 00:24:45.820
You didn't even invite us.

00:24:46.760 --> 00:24:48.080
There are no seats anyway.

00:24:48.080 --> 00:24:49.280
We didn't know.

00:24:49.280 --> 00:24:50.400
Alright, let's eat together.

00:24:50.400 --> 00:24:51.530
It's my treat today.

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:55.200
We probably won't have another chance.

00:24:59.720 --> 00:25:00.850
I forgot to tell you.

00:25:01.800 --> 00:25:02.600
I'm leaving.

00:25:03.880 --> 00:25:05.000
Mr. Li.

00:25:05.000 --> 00:25:06.130
Where are you going?

00:25:06.480 --> 00:25:07.600
Are you resigning?

00:25:08.200 --> 00:25:09.680
Mr. Li is getting married.

00:25:09.680 --> 00:25:12.400
Transferring to another position is his choice.

00:25:12.400 --> 00:25:15.200
You're leaving, yet you're still scaring Xiaoqu.

00:25:16.600 --> 00:25:17.560
Mr. Li.

00:25:17.560 --> 00:25:19.520
You must send me an invitation to your wedding.

00:25:19.520 --> 00:25:20.240
No problem.

00:25:22.240 --> 00:25:22.800
Come.

00:25:23.520 --> 00:25:23.960
Come.

00:25:23.960 --> 00:25:25.560
Congratulations to you all.

00:25:26.880 --> 00:25:29.080
You are now officially Muxing employees.

00:25:29.080 --> 00:25:29.760
Keep it up.

00:25:29.760 --> 00:25:30.800
Thank you, Mr. Li.

00:25:30.800 --> 00:25:31.520
Keep it up.

00:25:31.520 --> 00:25:32.580
Congratulations.

00:25:38.440 --> 00:25:39.840
Especially you, Xiaoqu.

00:25:41.200 --> 00:25:42.400
I was right about you.

00:25:43.320 --> 00:25:45.520
I believe you will have a better future.

00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:47.120
Thank you, Mr. Li.

00:25:49.200 --> 00:25:49.880
Tell me,

00:25:50.360 --> 00:25:52.080
regarding this four-to-one selection,

00:25:52.080 --> 00:25:53.360
did Mr. Qin and Mr. Gu

00:25:53.360 --> 00:25:55.000
set us up from the start?

00:25:55.000 --> 00:25:56.930
Just to motivate us to work harder,

00:25:57.160 --> 00:25:59.200
they put on a double act.

00:25:59.440 --> 00:26:01.640
Mr. Qin and Mr. Gu do love to play tricks.

00:26:01.800 --> 00:26:03.200
But this time, I heard...

00:26:03.400 --> 00:26:04.480
They pounded on the table

00:26:04.480 --> 00:26:05.560
to fight for you.

00:26:06.800 --> 00:26:07.920
Mr. Li and I always say

00:26:07.920 --> 00:26:09.120
how much we envy you.

00:26:09.640 --> 00:26:11.370
Mr. Qin really cares about you.

00:26:11.680 --> 00:26:12.800
Unlike back in our day,

00:26:12.800 --> 00:26:15.880
we had to hide behind the observatory to celebrate secretly.

00:26:15.880 --> 00:26:17.740
If we got caught, we'd be scolded.

00:26:17.880 --> 00:26:18.600
Yeah.

00:26:19.440 --> 00:26:21.120
Qin is much softer now.

00:26:21.280 --> 00:26:23.680
He used to be even more of a demon than Old Gu.

00:26:23.920 --> 00:26:25.360
We did this project over and over again.

00:26:25.360 --> 00:26:26.480
He just wouldn't pass it.

00:26:26.480 --> 00:26:28.560
I still remember the first time starting from scratch.

00:26:28.560 --> 00:26:30.220
I ate herbal jelly for a month.

00:26:30.360 --> 00:26:32.040
Just to teach myself a lesson.

00:26:32.600 --> 00:26:34.400
Never start from scratch again.

00:26:35.680 --> 00:26:36.600
Looks like

00:26:37.880 --> 00:26:40.140
I won't have the chance to eat it anymore.

00:26:46.280 --> 00:26:47.680
Let's change the subject.

00:26:47.680 --> 00:26:49.440
Well, I propose

00:26:49.440 --> 00:26:49.960
a toast.

00:26:50.440 --> 00:26:52.880
Happy wedding, senior.

00:26:53.320 --> 00:26:54.120
That's right.

00:26:54.120 --> 00:26:56.120
To a new department and a new life.

00:26:56.120 --> 00:26:57.720
Let's all congratulate Mr. Li together.

00:26:57.720 --> 00:26:59.880
Happy wedding, Mr. Li.

00:26:59.880 --> 00:27:02.240
Happy wedding.

00:27:02.240 --> 00:27:03.160
Come, Mr. Li.

00:27:03.160 --> 00:27:04.420
Happy wedding, Mr. Li.

00:27:09.000 --> 00:27:09.600
Cheers.

00:27:10.960 --> 00:27:11.760
Here's to you.

00:27:11.920 --> 00:27:12.980
Keep working hard.

00:27:13.600 --> 00:27:14.480
See you around.

00:28:27.480 --> 00:28:28.200
Slow down.

00:28:29.400 --> 00:28:30.040
Here.

00:28:30.400 --> 00:28:31.730
What is this place, Jia?

00:28:32.240 --> 00:28:34.320
This is Area 51 of the Space City.

00:28:34.320 --> 00:28:36.200
Only true star herders can come in.

00:28:36.200 --> 00:28:38.130
I'll broaden your horizons today.

00:28:47.440 --> 00:28:48.240
Be careful.

00:28:49.640 --> 00:28:50.570
Be careful, Nan.

00:28:51.200 --> 00:28:51.720
Cool.

00:29:00.320 --> 00:29:00.850
How is it?

00:29:03.720 --> 00:29:05.640
Why are there two handprints here?

00:29:05.640 --> 00:29:06.640
A blood oath?

00:29:09.400 --> 00:29:10.080
This is a bet

00:29:10.080 --> 00:29:12.000
Qin and Gu made back then.

00:29:12.560 --> 00:29:15.160
This was their secret base when they were young.

00:29:15.160 --> 00:29:15.800
A bet?

00:29:15.800 --> 00:29:16.930
About what? Who won?

00:29:18.040 --> 00:29:19.640
It was probably around 2004.

00:29:19.800 --> 00:29:20.600
At that time,

00:29:20.600 --> 00:29:23.260
our country's Haoyue Project had just started.

00:29:23.400 --> 00:29:25.200
It received a lot of international attention.

00:29:25.200 --> 00:29:26.120
Qin and Gu

00:29:26.120 --> 00:29:28.120
represented our flight control center

00:29:28.120 --> 00:29:30.800
to attend an international aerospace conference abroad.

00:29:30.800 --> 00:29:32.560
They thought it was an academic exchange,

00:29:32.560 --> 00:29:34.200
but it turned into a collective siege.

00:29:34.200 --> 00:29:35.400
They repeatedly questioned our

00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:37.200
orbit determination capability and technology.

00:29:37.200 --> 00:29:38.160
Besieged us?

00:29:38.440 --> 00:29:39.160
Why?

00:29:40.440 --> 00:29:41.640
The reason is simple.

00:29:42.040 --> 00:29:43.200
Because other countries

00:29:43.200 --> 00:29:45.120
had been doing lunar exploration for decades.

00:29:45.120 --> 00:29:47.380
We wanted to succeed in such a short time,

00:29:47.840 --> 00:29:49.770
and they thought we couldn't do it.

00:29:50.280 --> 00:29:52.480
So, Qin and Gu slammed the table,

00:29:52.480 --> 00:29:53.400
argued strongly,

00:29:53.400 --> 00:29:55.000
and had a big fight with them.

00:29:55.560 --> 00:29:57.320
Mr. Gu almost threw a punch.

00:29:58.360 --> 00:30:00.820
After they came back, they were disciplined

00:30:00.920 --> 00:30:02.120
and got scolded.

00:30:02.600 --> 00:30:03.840
But the old leader said

00:30:03.840 --> 00:30:05.680
the punishment was a matter of discipline.

00:30:05.680 --> 00:30:07.960
They were scolded because they didn't argue well,

00:30:07.960 --> 00:30:09.220
lacking the momentum.

00:30:13.920 --> 00:30:16.720
So they didn't believe we could pull it off.

00:30:17.640 --> 00:30:19.600
But we still proved them wrong.

00:30:20.320 --> 00:30:20.920
Exactly.

00:30:21.280 --> 00:30:23.720
So, that led to this bet.

00:30:23.720 --> 00:30:26.320
It's like an agreement between dream chasers.

00:30:38.560 --> 00:30:41.960
The Haoyue Project's orbiting, landing, and returning.

00:30:41.960 --> 00:30:45.290
It's worth it to accomplish just one thing in this lifetime.

00:30:46.760 --> 00:30:48.600
Actually, everyone who comes here

00:30:48.600 --> 00:30:49.760
is chasing a dream.

00:30:50.320 --> 00:30:51.800
Some chase it for five years,

00:30:51.800 --> 00:30:52.960
some for ten years,

00:30:53.200 --> 00:30:54.530
and some for a lifetime.

00:30:55.400 --> 00:30:57.560
Obstacles from reality are common.

00:30:58.120 --> 00:30:58.840
But

00:30:59.320 --> 00:31:02.040
we still need the courage to break through constraints

00:31:02.040 --> 00:31:03.640
and stay firm in our beliefs.

00:31:05.160 --> 00:31:06.160
I believe that

00:31:06.160 --> 00:31:08.820
as long as you've chased it, you won't regret it.

00:31:14.440 --> 00:31:15.120
Everyone.

00:31:16.360 --> 00:31:17.480
Shouldn't we also

00:31:17.480 --> 00:31:19.080
have some sort of agreement?

00:31:23.600 --> 00:31:24.960
Raoluohui.

00:31:27.520 --> 00:31:28.920
We are just one step away.

00:31:38.440 --> 00:31:39.120
Everyone,

00:31:39.120 --> 00:31:40.520
in this situation,

00:31:40.520 --> 00:31:42.640
I can't help but want to recite a poem.

00:31:44.520 --> 00:31:47.600
Wind and thunder stir, flags fly,

00:31:47.960 --> 00:31:49.160
it's the human world.

00:31:49.680 --> 00:31:51.540
Thirty-eight years have passed.

00:31:51.640 --> 00:31:53.440
In a mere flick of a finger.

00:31:54.680 --> 00:31:56.940
We can clasp the moon in the Ninth Heaven.

00:31:57.200 --> 00:31:59.530
And seize turtles deep in the Five Oceans.

00:31:59.800 --> 00:32:02.240
Returning amidst triumphant songs and laughter.

00:32:02.240 --> 00:32:04.560
Nothing is hard in this world

00:32:04.560 --> 00:32:06.640
if you dare to scale the heights.

00:32:07.120 --> 00:32:07.960
Good luck.

00:32:36.440 --> 00:32:37.000
Wake up.

00:32:37.840 --> 00:32:39.080
Get up. We're late.

00:33:12.360 --> 00:33:14.020
Why are you wearing slippers?

00:33:14.240 --> 00:33:16.300
Forget it. We are running out of time.

00:33:26.200 --> 00:33:27.260
Do your best today.

00:33:27.360 --> 00:33:28.240
Jia, Jia.

00:33:28.480 --> 00:33:29.000
Caibao.

00:33:31.080 --> 00:33:32.840
You look energetic today.

00:33:33.680 --> 00:33:35.480
Do I have the vibe of a Muxingren?

00:33:35.840 --> 00:33:36.360
No.

00:33:36.440 --> 00:33:37.480
Not bad.

00:33:38.200 --> 00:33:40.730
A Muxingren wouldn't wear slippers on stage.

00:33:42.040 --> 00:33:43.040
Everyone is here.

00:33:44.480 --> 00:33:46.200
You guys are full of energy.

00:33:46.200 --> 00:33:46.760
Youxiu,

00:33:47.680 --> 00:33:48.520
do me a favor.

00:33:48.760 --> 00:33:50.120
A favor? What favor?

00:33:50.680 --> 00:33:53.960
Congratulations on passing the probation assessment,

00:33:53.960 --> 00:33:57.000
and welcome to the flight control family.

00:34:07.480 --> 00:34:09.760
I remember I once asked you a question.

00:34:10.159 --> 00:34:11.400
The aerospace industry

00:34:11.400 --> 00:34:14.000
costs enormous human and material resources.

00:34:14.000 --> 00:34:16.120
What is its significance?

00:34:17.199 --> 00:34:20.199
I think after working here for a while,

00:34:20.760 --> 00:34:22.290
you have your own insights.

00:34:24.360 --> 00:34:26.040
I chose aerospace as my career,

00:34:26.040 --> 00:34:27.370
not for fame or fortune,

00:34:27.480 --> 00:34:28.600
but out of passion.

00:34:29.239 --> 00:34:31.000
Everyone in the Aerospace City

00:34:31.000 --> 00:34:32.159
is driven by ideals,

00:34:32.639 --> 00:34:34.969
moving forward step by step with passion.

00:34:35.360 --> 00:34:38.440
Passion itself is the meaning of passion.

00:34:40.920 --> 00:34:42.449
I actually really envy you.

00:34:42.840 --> 00:34:44.300
I envy that you have dreams

00:34:44.440 --> 00:34:45.480
to strive for.

00:34:46.760 --> 00:34:48.620
I even envy that you have pressure

00:34:48.760 --> 00:34:49.880
to motivate you.

00:34:50.600 --> 00:34:53.560
But I am like a satellite that failed to enter orbit.

00:34:56.719 --> 00:34:58.600
We must work hard to stay.

00:34:58.840 --> 00:34:59.680
Absolutely.

00:35:00.080 --> 00:35:01.740
We're meant for big missions.

00:35:02.160 --> 00:35:03.880
We'll personally send rockets and satellites

00:35:03.880 --> 00:35:04.880
into space.

00:35:07.160 --> 00:35:08.240
Someone once said

00:35:08.520 --> 00:35:10.040
that it's impossible for the Chinese.

00:35:10.040 --> 00:35:12.320
who sent satellites into space.

00:35:12.680 --> 00:35:14.680
Back then, our country had nothing.

00:35:15.000 --> 00:35:18.120
It was our predecessors who used their hands

00:35:18.120 --> 00:35:20.720
to send satellites into space bit by bit,

00:35:20.840 --> 00:35:23.960
turning the impossible into the possible.

00:35:25.080 --> 00:35:27.480
We went from trailing behind others

00:35:27.800 --> 00:35:28.600
to now,

00:35:28.960 --> 00:35:31.490
about to become the first country in the world

00:35:31.920 --> 00:35:33.840
to land on the far side of the moon.

00:35:33.920 --> 00:35:36.040
Generations of our aerospace workers

00:35:36.040 --> 00:35:39.160
have persevered and worked hard

00:35:40.680 --> 00:35:42.410
to make it this far step by step.

00:35:43.400 --> 00:35:45.680
Lao Gu and I,

00:35:46.680 --> 00:35:49.040
we will eventually grow old.

00:35:49.040 --> 00:35:51.240
Even you will grow old.

00:35:51.920 --> 00:35:53.080
But I believe

00:35:53.280 --> 00:35:54.480
when that time comes,

00:35:54.720 --> 00:35:56.320
you will be just like us,

00:35:56.320 --> 00:35:59.560
proudly passing on the baton.

00:36:02.080 --> 00:36:03.440
The human lifespan,

00:36:03.440 --> 00:36:05.440
compared to the timescale of the universe,

00:36:05.440 --> 00:36:06.560
is so tiny.

00:36:07.760 --> 00:36:10.920
Then why do aerospace workers spend their whole lives,

00:36:11.360 --> 00:36:13.420
devoting our limited human lifespan

00:36:13.640 --> 00:36:15.360
to the infinite universe,

00:36:15.360 --> 00:36:18.080
to conquer it generation by generation?

00:36:19.080 --> 00:36:21.000
Whether the first attempt is a success or a failure,

00:36:21.000 --> 00:36:22.200
it has already begun.

00:36:23.840 --> 00:36:26.000
I want you to remember this moment.

00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:28.660
Right now, the way you feel at this exact moment.

00:36:29.880 --> 00:36:30.560
Remember,

00:36:32.520 --> 00:36:35.120
it will stay with you for the rest of your lives.

00:36:44.640 --> 00:36:46.560
One, two, three, cheese!

00:36:47.720 --> 00:36:49.120
Good. One more, one more.

00:36:49.720 --> 00:36:52.280
One, two, three, cheese!

00:36:53.560 --> 00:36:54.280
Alright, alright, alright.

00:36:54.280 --> 00:36:55.720
Let me take a picture with Sister Jia.

00:36:55.720 --> 00:36:56.980
That's not necessary.

00:36:57.160 --> 00:36:58.040
On such a great day,

00:36:58.040 --> 00:36:59.360
I must take a picture with Sister Jia.

00:36:59.360 --> 00:37:00.620
Come on, let's take it.

00:37:01.520 --> 00:37:02.960
One, two, three.

00:37:03.400 --> 00:37:04.080
All right.

00:37:05.200 --> 00:37:06.200
How was the shoot?

00:37:06.280 --> 00:37:07.610
It was really well shot,

00:37:07.840 --> 00:37:08.570
to be honest.

00:37:08.680 --> 00:37:09.120
Jia,

00:37:09.120 --> 00:37:10.180
it's so emotional.

00:37:11.120 --> 00:37:12.240
Without Mr. Qian,

00:37:13.440 --> 00:37:15.770
we wouldn't have our achievements today.

00:37:17.560 --> 00:37:18.240
Wei,

00:37:18.760 --> 00:37:20.160
last time I went to the archives

00:37:20.160 --> 00:37:21.640
to check the fault plans,

00:37:21.640 --> 00:37:23.880
I also saw an identical one.

00:37:23.880 --> 00:37:25.680
Your myopia must have deepened.

00:37:26.440 --> 00:37:28.040
The same style as Mr. Qian's.

00:37:28.040 --> 00:37:29.560
Limited edition worldwide.

00:37:29.560 --> 00:37:30.420
It must be fake.

00:37:30.560 --> 00:37:31.720
Were you deceived,

00:37:31.720 --> 00:37:33.040
and now trying to deceive us?

00:37:33.040 --> 00:37:35.720
Sour grapes.

00:37:36.040 --> 00:37:36.560
Brother Wei,

00:37:36.560 --> 00:37:38.120
why are you acting like Mr. Qin now?

00:37:38.120 --> 00:37:39.080
Just like an old fox,

00:37:39.080 --> 00:37:40.000
full of tricks.

00:37:42.920 --> 00:37:43.960
Where are you going?

00:37:43.960 --> 00:37:44.890
To find Mr. Zhao.

00:37:45.240 --> 00:37:47.200
I heard Mr. Zhao is about to retire.

00:37:54.640 --> 00:37:55.900
You two playing chess?

00:38:08.400 --> 00:38:09.880
Oh no, we're busted.

00:38:10.360 --> 00:38:11.690
It's all because of you.

00:38:12.800 --> 00:38:13.600
Because of me?

00:38:20.720 --> 00:38:21.360
Wu Wei.

00:38:21.880 --> 00:38:23.210
What are you doing here?

00:38:25.440 --> 00:38:26.160
Mr. Zhao.

00:38:26.840 --> 00:38:29.080
Aerospace workers don't lie to aerospace workers.

00:38:29.080 --> 00:38:31.200
Is this Mr. Qian's pen or not?

00:38:33.480 --> 00:38:34.960
Well...

00:38:35.480 --> 00:38:36.800
Why wouldn't it be?

00:38:36.800 --> 00:38:38.440
This is Mr. Qian's pen.

00:38:38.920 --> 00:38:40.580
This pen... of course it is...

00:38:40.640 --> 00:38:41.880
Mr. Qian's, right?

00:38:42.080 --> 00:38:43.920
Why would I lie to you?

00:38:46.040 --> 00:38:46.640
No.

00:38:47.960 --> 00:38:49.200
Let me put it this way.

00:38:50.480 --> 00:38:51.160
Um...

00:38:51.560 --> 00:38:54.240
Mr. Qin did this for you

00:38:54.240 --> 00:38:56.170
so you can become more successful.

00:38:57.160 --> 00:38:58.040
I'm telling you,

00:38:58.040 --> 00:38:59.840
for your sake,

00:38:59.840 --> 00:39:02.400
he really went to great lengths.

00:39:02.800 --> 00:39:04.560
You can't let him down.

00:39:06.640 --> 00:39:08.400
Aren't you just playing with my feelings?

00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:09.160
Kid,

00:39:09.840 --> 00:39:10.680
watch your words.

00:39:10.680 --> 00:39:12.040
What do you mean, playing with your feelings?

00:39:12.040 --> 00:39:13.240
Is the pen important?

00:39:13.360 --> 00:39:16.420
The important thing is the inheritance and the spirit.

00:39:17.600 --> 00:39:18.320
Got it?

00:39:22.000 --> 00:39:23.640
What about your retirement?

00:39:23.640 --> 00:39:24.900
Why didn't you tell me?

00:39:27.160 --> 00:39:28.090
What do you mean?

00:39:28.840 --> 00:39:29.900
Does my retirement

00:39:30.520 --> 00:39:31.840
have to go through you?

00:39:33.080 --> 00:39:35.540
You shouldn't have just left without a word.

00:39:35.840 --> 00:39:38.240
You said there are no cowards in the archives.

00:39:38.240 --> 00:39:39.560
The mission isn't over yet.

00:39:39.560 --> 00:39:41.000
How could you retreat first?

00:39:41.000 --> 00:39:41.720
Besides,

00:39:42.080 --> 00:39:43.840
I think you can still work.

00:39:45.360 --> 00:39:46.840
What can I do?

00:39:50.000 --> 00:39:51.760
I'm almost seventy.

00:39:52.320 --> 00:39:54.440
I've worked here my whole life.

00:39:54.560 --> 00:39:55.280
What?

00:39:55.800 --> 00:39:57.400
Do you want to squeeze me dry?

00:39:59.800 --> 00:40:02.080
Even a donkey at the mill

00:40:02.080 --> 00:40:03.800
needs a break.

00:40:03.800 --> 00:40:05.600
Can't you let me catch my breath?

00:40:07.200 --> 00:40:07.840
Okay.

00:40:08.760 --> 00:40:09.400
Alright.

00:40:09.760 --> 00:40:10.720
Don't just stand there.

00:40:10.720 --> 00:40:12.250
You're holding up our game.

00:40:15.600 --> 00:40:16.600
I'm leaving then.

00:40:18.920 --> 00:40:19.560
Go ahead.

00:40:27.320 --> 00:40:28.120
Wait a minute.

00:40:54.400 --> 00:40:55.000
Wu Wei.

00:40:58.520 --> 00:41:00.160
Now,

00:41:00.160 --> 00:41:03.280
I solemnly hand this pen over to you.

00:41:07.000 --> 00:41:07.920
As for you,

00:41:07.920 --> 00:41:09.760
you came from my place after all.

00:41:10.640 --> 00:41:11.880
You must work hard.

00:41:12.920 --> 00:41:14.050
Don't embarrass me.

00:41:14.080 --> 00:41:14.880
Hear me?

00:41:24.760 --> 00:41:25.840
Don't worry.

00:41:38.720 --> 00:41:39.880
You brat.

00:41:43.440 --> 00:41:45.560
Old Qin, Comrade Qin.

00:41:47.040 --> 00:41:48.500
I'm returning this to you.

00:41:48.720 --> 00:41:50.600
You... you keep it.

00:41:51.280 --> 00:41:52.560
Why would I keep it?

00:41:52.920 --> 00:41:53.840
You'd better keep it yourself.

00:41:53.840 --> 00:41:55.240
What if I send you another trainee?

00:41:55.240 --> 00:41:56.360
Why would you do that?

00:41:56.360 --> 00:41:57.320
I'm already retired.

00:41:57.320 --> 00:41:58.580
Who else could I trick?

00:42:01.320 --> 00:42:04.520
It looks like we won't be able to finish this game of chess.

00:42:08.440 --> 00:42:09.040
Old Qin.

00:42:11.360 --> 00:42:14.280
I feel like doing one thing for a whole lifetime,

00:42:14.720 --> 00:42:16.600
time goes by so fast.

00:42:17.600 --> 00:42:18.460
Playing chess?

00:42:18.800 --> 00:42:19.480
Aerospace.

